name: Picacho del Diablo
description:
Introduction

This location and peak is called a POI (Point of Interest) and not rated. But this peak and surrounding Peaks, Canyons, rock walls, and such, offer many places where technicals skills can be used. And such technical skills will assist the adventurer out there while exploring this area. A very remote and wild place to test yourself.

Including a lot of "Up-Canyoneering" to deal with. And rock climbing sections. Probably would be ranked among one of the wildest adventures spots in N America. This Peak has it all for people looking to escape and test their abilities in a rugged, remote and very spectacular playground - Peaks, rock climbing, canyons, navigation skills, backcountry expedition skills, etc.

Approach

The map and trip reports are showing the two main ways to get to this peak. The West side from the Pacific Ocean. And the East side from the Sea of Cortez. You can pick which option to do. Only showing the two main ways to get there. Other options are also available, and not being shown here.

Descent

THe Route known as "Pinnacle Ridge" is considered a technical trip, with 5th Class terrain to deal with. So ropes and hardware are advised if attempted. Or gamble with un-roped free-solo climbing and descending the cliff-bands along the way.

Exit

Red tape
